assignee.description:
Approver expression (only effective for UserTask nodes; gateway / event nodes do not support), corresponding to flowable:assignee attribute, such as: ${initiator}. The assignee field is only used for 【single approver】 scenarios, and its expression must satisfy: 1. Expression execution result type: String (single user ID) 2. Strictly prohibited to return: Array / List / multiple user IDs. You can use ${Array.first(User.superiorUsers(initiator))} like this. 3. If you need to use arrays, you cannot use array literals, but must use Array.of to construct arrays.

❌ Error example (will definitely report an error):
${Array.first(User.usersWithRole(['researcher']))}

✅ Correct example:
${Array.first(User.usersWithRole(Array.of('researcher')))}
4.【User field reference rules】
- If using user fields in the form:
  - Single-select user field: ${form.projectManager.id}
  - Multi-select user field: Must use Array.first(...) to get one user
